---
@version: [2, current]
@description: Convert relative URL into full URL.
@lot: string $path = "", $root = true
@static: 1
@example: |
  $A = URL::long("");
  $B = URL::long('foo');
  $C = URL::long('?foo');
  $D = URL::long('&foo');
  $E = URL::long('#foo');
  $F = URL::long('javascript:;');
  $G = URL::long('foo/bar');
  $H = URL::long('?foo&bar');
  $I = URL::long('&foo&bar');
  $J = URL::long('//foo');
  $K = URL::long('http://foo');
  $L = URL::long('/');
  $M = URL::long('/foo');
  $N = URL::long('/?foo');
  $O = URL::long('/&foo');
  $P = URL::long('/#foo');
  $Q = URL::long('/javascript:;');
  $R = URL::long('/foo/bar');
  $S = URL::long('/?foo&bar');
  $T = URL::long('/&foo&bar');
@result: |
  $A = '[[e]]echo URL::long("");[[/e]]';
  $B = '[[e]]echo URL::long('foo');[[/e]]';
  $C = '[[e]]echo URL::long('?foo');[[/e]]';
  $D = '[[e]]echo URL::long('&foo');[[/e]]';
  $E = '[[e]]echo URL::long('#foo');[[/e]]';
  $F = '[[e]]echo URL::long('javascript:;');[[/e]]';
  $G = '[[e]]echo URL::long('foo/bar');[[/e]]';
  $H = '[[e]]echo URL::long('?foo&bar');[[/e]]';
  $I = '[[e]]echo URL::long('&foo&bar');[[/e]]';
  $J = '[[e]]echo URL::long('//foo');[[/e]]';
  $K = '[[e]]echo URL::long('http://foo');[[/e]]';
  $L = '[[e]]echo URL::long('/');[[/e]]';
  $M = '[[e]]echo URL::long('/foo');[[/e]]';
  $N = '[[e]]echo URL::long('/?foo');[[/e]]';
  $O = '[[e]]echo URL::long('/&foo');[[/e]]';
  $P = '[[e]]echo URL::long('/#foo');[[/e]]';
  $Q = '[[e]]echo URL::long('/javascript:;');[[/e]]';
  $R = '[[e]]echo URL::long('/foo/bar');[[/e]]';
  $S = '[[e]]echo URL::long('/?foo&bar');[[/e]]';
  $T = '[[e]]echo URL::long('/&foo&bar');[[/e]]';
@result-note: If `$root` is `false`, then a `/` character at the beginning of URL path will be ignored, and the result will always relative to the URL path where the CMS is being installed. The `$root` parameter changes makes sense only when Mecha is installed in a sub-directory.
